      <opener>
        <salute>Dear Sir, </salute>
      </opener>
      <p>I beg to let you know that I have on account of Mr Matsukata the following works: </p>
      <p>Charles Cottet : </p>
      <p>    &#8226; L&#8217;office du soir [12 000 : ce montant est &#233;crit au crayon &#224; papier, comme les autres]</p>
      <p>    &#8226; Procession &#224; Plougastel [6000]</p>
      <p>    &#8226; Venise, vue des jardins [4000]</p>
      <p>    &#8226; L&#8217;anse de St Guinol&#233;, (temps de pluie) [3000]</p>
      <p>    &#8226; Le Tage &#224; Tol&#232;de, (temps de pluie) [2500]</p>
      <p>    &#8226; La boucle du Tage &#224; Tol&#232;de [2500]</p>
      <p>Peintures</p>
      <p>Auguste Pointelin : </p>
      <p>    &#8226; Le Vallon, Jura</p>
      <p>    &#8226; Clair de lune, Jura</p>
      <p>    &#8226; Solitude</p>
      <p>    &#8226; Le ruisseau, Jura</p>
      <p>Peintures</p>
      <p>Henri Harpignies : </p>
      <p>    &#8226; Au bord de l&#8217;eau [&#173;]</p>
      <p>Peinture</p>
      <p>[Total 52 000]</p>
      <p>These pictures are deposed at H&#244;tel Biron, in the name of Mr Matsukata,for whom I join to this letter a certificate that will justify his right of property. All the works that belong to Mr Matsukata will be placed together in the same room, and each of them will be labelled.</p>
      <p>I pursue my other negociations, and I beg you in regard of these works to kindly let me have the 52,000 francs they represent.</p>
      <closer>
        <salute>Yours truly</salute>
      </closer>
    </body>
